=> DO NOT FOLLOW => Replacing Unity with XFCE in Ubuntu

Perform all of these as root in a terminal window, or prepend with sudo. (Look elsewhere for GUI steps 🙂 )

    Update your repos:

    apt-get update

    Uninstall Unity and ubuntu-desktop:
    
    sudo apt-get remove nautilus nautilus-* gnome-power-manager gnome-screensaver gnome-termina* gnome-pane* gnome-applet* gnome-bluetooth gnome-desktop* gnome-sessio* gnome-user* gnome-shell-common zeitgeist-core libzeitgeist* gnome-control-center gnome-screenshot gnome* && sudo apt-get autoremove

    apt-get purge ubuntu-desktop unity-*

    Install XFCE Desktop environment:
    
    sudo apt install xubuntu-desktop
    apt-get install xfce4
    
    To enable XFCE on boot time:
    
    echo “xfce4-session” > ~/.xsession

    Restart lightdm:

    /etc/init.d/lightdm restart

Voilà! You’re using XFCE desktop! 😉
